column5: Nice one that things a fatty Thx Freshtrax, even my son and I could not finish one fillet lol

Beauty John. WTG!!!  It's been tropical down south there in Yellowknife this year. lol.  Don't blame ya one bit for taking full advantage.  Wouldn't be right not to.  Get out there and do it again.  Clear -35°C FEELS LIKE -52  Thx Bunk, your getting slammed with some of the winter we are missing , the trout was a dink compared to the ones you connect with while guiding on the big lake, but getting that one on one of the lakes off the Trail, well I was pretty stoked, definitely my biggest so far,  It is crazy good to be fishing quite often with your sled suit on but your parka undone, like fishing on Lake Simcoe lol  As u know -20 or 25 feels balmy, no hut needed  Be good , be safe up there , talk to u soon
